'''Ferdi Erenay Kadıoğlu''' ({{IPA|tr|fæɾˈdi eɾeˈnaj kaˈdɯoːɫu}}; born 7 October 1999) is a  professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[full-back (association football)|full back]], [[midfielder]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|Brigh&HA}} club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]]. He is known for his versatility, being able to play in multiple positions on both sides of the field.<ref>{{cite web |date=30 January 2026 |title=Ferdi Kadioglu: Meet the Premier League’s most versatile player |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/ferdi-kadioglu-brighton-premier-league-cstr3m2mr |access-date=11 May 2026 |work=The Times}}</ref>

Kadıoğlu began his professional career at [[NEC Nijmegen|NEC]] in 2016, where he played in two seasons for the team, before moving to [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] in 2018, spending six years in [[Süper Lig]]. He then joined English club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in 2024.

Kadıoğlu made his senior international debut for Turkey in 2022 and was part of their squad at the [[UEFA European Championship]] in [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]], where they made a surprise run to the quarter-finals.

==Club career==
===NEC===
====2016–2017 season====
Kadıoğlu spent his early years with [[NEC Nijmegen|NEC]]. On 28 August 2016, he made his professional debut as a late substitute against [[AZ Alkmaar]] in a 2–0 away loss. In his first professional year, he scored 4 goals and made 4 assists in 27 (9 starts) [[Eredivisie]] matches. NEC finished the season in 16th position and were relegated to the [[Eerste Divisie]] after the relegation play-off. Kadıoğlu also played 3 relegation play-off matches.

====2017–2018 season====
In his second professional year with the team, Kadıoğlu remained a key part of the squad. He scored 7 goals and made 12 assists in 34 (31 starts) Eerste Divisie matches. NEC finished the season in 3rd place but weren't promoted to Eredivisie after losing against [[FC Emmen|Emmen]] in the promotion play-offs. Kadıoğlu also played 3 promotion second round playoff matches.

===Fenerbahçe===
====2018–2020: Signing and emergence====
[[File:Ferdi Kadioglu (2021-22 Süper Lig) - Resim2 (cropped).png|thumb|upright|Kadıoğlu before a match in 2021]]
In July 2018, Kadıoğlu signed for Turkish [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-07-14 |title=Fenerbahce sign Ferdi Kadioglu from NEC - Turkish Football News |url=https://www.turkishfootballnews.com/2018/07/14/fenerbahce-sign-ferdi-kadioglu-nec/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127013704/https://www.turkishfootballnews.com/2018/07/14/fenerbahce-sign-ferdi-kadioglu-nec/ |archive-date=2021-11-27 |access-date=2025-06-15 |work=Turkish Football News |language=en-US}}</ref> He made his debut for the senior squad on 20 December 2018, coming on as a substitute in a [[Turkish Cup]] match against [[Giresunspor]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kadioglu after five months debut for Fenerbahçe in bekerduel|url=https://www.firstorderhistorians.com/2018/12/20/kadioglu-after-five-months-debut-for-fenerbahce-in-bekerduel/|date=20 December 2018|access-date=27 November 2021|archive-date=8 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230208144651/https://www.firstorderhistorians.com/2018/12/20/kadioglu-after-five-months-debut-for-fenerbahce-in-bekerduel/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In his first season, he played mostly for the [[Fenerbahçe S.K. U21|under-21]] team, making 11 appearances with them in the [[U21 Ligi]].

The following season he started to find more time in the senior squad and scored his first goal for Fenerbahçe on 19 August 2019 against [[Gaziantep F.K.|Gaziantep]], netting the final goal in a 5–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/fenerbahce-trounce-gazisehir-gaziantep-5-0-145900|date=20 August 2019|title=Fenerbahçe trounce Gazişehir Gaziantep 5–0|access-date=27 November 2021|archive-date=27 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127013702/https://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/fenerbahce-trounce-gazisehir-gaziantep-5-0-145900|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2020–2022: Increased playing time====
In his third season, under new manager [[Erol Bulut]], he started to find more time in first team and became one of the key players who took more responsibility on the field.

In the subsequent year, with changes in management, first under [[Vítor Pereira (footballer, born 1968)|Vitor Pereira]] and then [[İsmail Kartal]], he solidified his starter role. Despite his age, he consistently earned and played full 90-minute matches.

On 17 March 2022, Fenerbahçe announced that they had signed a four-year contract with Kadıoğlu until June 2026.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Fenerbahçe Yolunuz Açık Olsun… Armamızla, Uzun Yıllar Nice Başarılara - Fenerbahçe SK |trans-title=May your path be open, Fenerbahçe… To many more successes for long years with our crest – Fenerbahçe SK |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/3/fenerbahce-yolunuz-acik-olsun%E2%80%A6-armamizla-uzun-yillar-nice-basarilara |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220420001221/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/3/fenerbahce-yolunuz-acik-olsun%E2%80%A6-armamizla-uzun-yillar-nice-basarilara |archive-date=2022-04-20 |access-date=2025-06-15}}</ref>

====2022–2024: Key player====
In his fifth season, he emerged as a versatile player for Fenerbahçe, occupying multiple positions in the first eleven, mainly at both full-back positions. He finished the season with 4 goals and 5 assists across all competitions, amassing a total of 4,175 minutes of playtime.

In his sixth season, he made a very strong start with new coach and club legend İsmail Kartal.

===Brighton and Hove Albion===
On 27 August 2024, Kadıoğlu joined [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] for a reported fee of £25m, with an additional £4.2m in add-ons. He signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ferdi Kadioglu: Brighton sign Turkey full-back from Fenerbahce for £25m |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cly85ryg3z9o |work=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2024}}</ref>

On 18 September 2024, Kadıoğlu scored his first goal for Brighton in a 3–2 victory over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in the third round of the [[2024–25 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Brighton 3-2 Wolves: Carlos Baleba, Simon Adingra score in Carabao Cup |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c07ney4yy0kt |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 2 November, he scored his first Premier League goal in a 2–1 defeat to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Liverpool 2–1 Brighton & Hove Albion |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6k5e2y8llt |work=BBC Sport |date=2 November 2024 |access-date=3 November 2024}}</ref>

On 19 May 2026, Kadıoğlu was named the Brighton and Hove Albion player of the year for the [[2025–26 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2025–26]] season.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/media-article/ferdi-and-fran-win-player-of-the-season-awards | title=Ferdi and Fran win player of the season awards }}</ref>

==International career==
Kadıoğlu was born in the Netherlands to a Turkish father and a [[Dutch Canadians|Dutch Canadian]] mother.<ref>{{cite web |title=Familie ziet scorende Kadioglu schitteren |trans-title=Family sees scoring Kadioglu shine. |url=https://www.gelderlander.nl/sport/familie-ziet-scorende-kadioglu-schitteren~a0d1e8f2/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102123206/http://www.gelderlander.nl/sport/nec/familie-ziet-scorende-kadioglu-schitteren-1.6591233 |archive-date=2 November 2016 |access-date=19 June 2017 |website=gelderlander.nl |language=nl}}</ref> He was therefore eligible to represent [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]], the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] internationally.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ferdi Kadıoğlu: Türkiye, Hollanda veya Kanada'yı seçme hakkım var |trans-title=Ferdi Kadıoğlu: I have a right to choose Turkey, Netherlands or Canada |url=https://www.goal.com/tr/haber/ferdi-kadioglu-tuerkiye-hollanda-veya-kanadayi-secme-hakkim/1o6fw7udeb6531fosgr8plnxcb |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205213824/https://www.goal.com/tr/haber/ferdi-kadioglu-tuerkiye-hollanda-veya-kanadayi-secme-hakkim/1o6fw7udeb6531fosgr8plnxcb |archive-date=2021-02-05 |access-date=2025-06-15 |language=tr}}</ref> He was a youth international for the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Under-17 - Ferdi Kadioglu – UEFA.com |url=http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2016/teams/player=250091943/index.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017154006/http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2016/teams/player=250091943/index.html |archive-date=2017-10-17 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> In March 2021, Kadıoğlu was named to the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands U-21]] squad for that year's [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-03-17 |title=Profiled: The Netherlands squad for the U21 European Championships - Football Oranje |url=http://www.football-oranje.com/profiled-the-netherlands-squad-for-the-u21-european-championships/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127015836/http://www.football-oranje.com/profiled-the-netherlands-squad-for-the-u21-european-championships/ |archive-date=2021-11-27 |access-date=2025-06-15 |work=Football Oranje |language=en-US}}</ref> Later that year on 12 November 2021, Turkey coach [[Stefan Kuntz]] revealed that he was expecting Kadıoğlu to make his decision on his international future in March 2022.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sporx |date=2021-11-12 |title=Stefan Kuntz'tan Ferdi Kadıoğlu açıklaması |trans-title=Stefan Kuntz's statement about Ferdi Kadıoğlu |url=https://www.sporx.com/stefan-kuntz-tan-ferdi-kadioglu-aciklamasi-SXHBQ948826SXQ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231030061959/https://www.sporx.com/stefan-kuntz-tan-ferdi-kadioglu-aciklamasi-SXHBQ948826SXQ |archive-date=2023-10-30 |access-date=2025-06-15 |work=Sporx.com |language=tr-TR}}</ref> On 3 January 2022, his club Fenerbahçe announced that he had chosen to represent the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ferdi Kadıoğlu'nun tercihi resmiyet kazandı -  Milli Takımlar Haber Detay Sayfası TFF |trans-title=Ferdi Kadıoğlu's choice became official - National Teams News Detail Page TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=628&ftxtID=36921 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121222748/https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=628&ftxtID=36921 |archive-date=2022-01-21 |access-date=2025-06-15 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Ferdi Kadıoğlu’na Türk Milli Takımımızla Sonsuz Başarılar Dileriz - Fenerbahçe SK |trans-title=We wish Ferdi Kadıoğlu endless success with our Turkish National Team - Fenerbahçe SK |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/1/ferdi-kadioglu-na-turk-milli-takimimizla-sonsuz-basarilar-dileriz |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220103164522/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2022/1/ferdi-kadioglu-na-turk-milli-takimimizla-sonsuz-basarilar-dileriz |archive-date=2022-01-03 |access-date=2025-06-15}}</ref> On 4 June 2022, Kadıoğlu debuted with Turkey in a 4–0 [[UEFA Nations League]] win over the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Türkiye Faroe Adaları maçı öncesi Stefan Kuntz’tan Ferdi Kadıoğlu yorumu! |trans-title=Stefan Kuntz's comment on Ferdi Kadıoğlu ahead of the Turkey vs. Faroe Islands match! |url=https://www.fotomac.com.tr/millitakim/2022/06/04/turkiye-faroe-adalari-maci-oncesi-stefan-kuntztan-ferdi-kadioglu-yorumu |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605061828/https://www.fotomac.com.tr/millitakim/2022/06/04/turkiye-faroe-adalari-maci-oncesi-stefan-kuntztan-ferdi-kadioglu-yorumu |archive-date=2022-06-05 |access-date=2025-06-15 |work=Fotomaç}}</ref> On 18 November 2023, he scored his first international goal in a 3–2 friendly win over [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in Berlin.<ref>{{Cite news |title=A Milli Futbol Takımı'nda Ferdi Kadıoğlu fırtınası! Berlin'de şov yaptı |trans-title=A Ferdi Kadıoğlu storm in the A National Football Team! He put on a show in Berlin. |url=https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/a-milli-futbol-takiminda-ferdi-kadioglu-firtinasi-berlinde-sov-yapti-7036653 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119131234/https://www.milliyet.com.tr/skorer/a-milli-futbol-takiminda-ferdi-kadioglu-firtinasi-berlinde-sov-yapti-7036653 |archive-date=2023-11-19 |access-date=2025-06-15 |work=Milliyet |language=tr}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, Kadıoğlu was named in Turkey's squad by coach [[Vincenzo Montella]] for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 Candidate Squad of Our National Team Announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44561 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=3 November 2024}}</ref>

